11/01/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The international community on Wednesday (January 10th) called for a peaceful, free and fair mayoral vote Sunday in the mainly ethnic Albanian-populated municipality of Saraj. The election was scheduled after the incumbent, Imer Selmani, was appointed to serve as health minister in the new government. In separate statements Wednesday, the ambassadors of the European Commission, the United States and Germany called for calm, stressing that the vote would represent another opportunity for Macedonia to demonstrate its ability to hold elections according to international standards. (Vecer - 11/01/07; MIA, Telma TV - 10/01/07)
